    <h4>Exercise</h4>
    <p>In the exercise on the next page, we will think about different situations, what we are thinking about in response to those situations (self-talk), and our stress level.</p>

    <p class="toBold">Behavior Log</p>

    <p><span class="toBold">Description: </span>A Behavior Log allows us to document when a certain behavior took place, how the behavior made us feel, and the stress level we were experiencing during the behavior. It enables us to see which behaviors and thoughts make us have lower and higher stress levels.</p>

    <p><span class="toBold">Instructions: </span>In the Behavior Log on the next page, look at the examples of how to document behaviors, how they made you feel, and your stress level. Then, either on the page or a separate piece of paper, make your own Behavior Log. Write the day, time, situation, what you are thinking, and your stress level.</p>

